					<p>Hej Mirko,</p>
<p>I guess in your special case you have to use a font-editor (like Fontforge) and do the subsetting by hand for now. We&#8217;re might add per-character-subsetting to Fontie some day, but right now there&#8217;s just too much other stuff we have to code. It might be a good idea to follow <a href="http://facebook.com/flowyapps" rel="nofollow">Flowy Apps on Facebook</a> or <a href="http://twitter.com/flowyapps" rel="nofollow">on Twitter</a> to be informed, when new Fontie-feature arrive.</p>
<p>Regarding your other question I recommend to read the <a href="http://www.smashingmagazine.com/2012/04/24/a-closer-look-at-font-rendering/" rel="nofollow">Smashing article on font rendering I&#8217;ve linked in the article</a>. This explains all the basics and the rest is just trial and error ;P</p>
<p>Bai<br />
Torben</p>
